    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. but some people argue that the veto power isn't really a \"flaw\" but actually the only thing that keeps the big powers from just walking away entirely, like making the system actually functional. do historians see that as a valid argument or is that just seen as an excuse for why nothing gets done?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
