      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Historians recognize the veto power as a necessary evil that reflects the current geopolitical reality, but they don't view it as a virtue. It functions as a guardrail, preventing the UN from becoming a tool for unilateral aggression by a single superpower. However, this \"functionality\" comes at the cost of genuine global security, as the veto allows major powers to prioritize national interest over international peace. Ultimately, it is seen as the system's most glaring, self-imposed weakness.",
      "source": "target",
